<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{3}{y}=-{22}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{7}{y}=-{32}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of --9. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle--\frac{{9}}{{-{{8}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{-{9}}}{{-{{8}}}}{\left(-{8}{x}+{3}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{-{9}}}{{-{{8}}}}{\left(-{22}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left(-{9}\right)}{x}+-{3.375}{y}={24.75}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{7}{y}=-{32}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3.625}{y}=-{7.25}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{7.25}}{{3.625}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{3}{\left(-{2}\right)}=-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{\left(-{6}\right)}=-{22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{22}-{\left(-{6}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{16}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

